##After the infection, he chose to go home to the fever patients online, leaving the bed for the patients

Lifeweek

Features an introduction to a magazine and the life he advocates.

17 years in medicine,
As a doctor at the emergency center of Wuhan's No. 3 Hospital, Li Chun felt "more helpless than ever. ".
Image | visual China
He had been exposed to a wide range of highly infectious diseases clinically and had never been afraid of them. But when he learned that he had been diagnosed with COVID-19 pneumonia, which he later passed on to his wife, daughters, and in laws, he became frightened and, for the first time, suspicious of himself, "As a doctor, you can't protect your family. Who Do you think you can protect? "

At a time when all hospitals in Wuhan were running low on beds, Li Chun decided not to take up other patients'beds. The good news is, he's in recovery, and his family is currently experiencing mild symptoms.

During the home quarantine, Li Chun insisted on consulting online for patients with fevers. The upper limit on the number of patients coming in for consultation is being updated day by day. He knew that if it was new pneumonia, such a visit was unlikely to help patients in any practical way, but it would be nice to give even a glimmer of hope to the "terrified and helpless" .

Li Chun shared with us one of the most frightening moments of his life. Here's what he said:


1


On January 8,2020, the emergency center of my hospital was used as a fever ward, where patients with severe fevers were kept for three days for nucleic acid testing to determine if they were infected with COVID-19.

We had 15 beds in our emergency center, and at first we could barely keep up with fever, and the clinic needed The Adventure of the Resident Patient. But with the development of the epidemic, to January 10, the daily need to be hospitalized in the acute severe cases of 30-50 patients, and our normal full bed can only admit 22 people.

That's when my colleagues and I started working around the clock. Over 80 paramedics, most of whom never made it home. Spring Festival is also spent in the hospital. Protective clothing is inconvenient to wear, in order to reduce the need to go to the bathroom, we do not dare to drink more water, hungry to eat hospital meals, sleepy hospital in rest area to deal with.

On January 18, I started to have a fever and cough, but the CT was normal. I think I'm just a upper respiratory tract infection, just a cold. I just need to rest. But two or three days later, after nucleic acid testing and imaging, I was diagnosed.

Now that I think about it, it's probably because of the unprotected exposure between January 5th and 8th. On Jan. 5, we treated a 61-year-old man with severe pneumonia who had been referred from a county hospital. According to the diagnostic criteria of the time, patients had to have a history of exposure to the south China Seafood Market to be considered for NCP. But not this patient. We just put him in isolation for severe pneumonia.

Unexpectedly, later I and 3 nurses in the same group all won the bid.

Due to the rapid development of the disease, our hospital beds are very tight, some patients need to wait a few days to be admitted to the hospital, in order not to occupy hospital bed resources, I decided to go home self-isolation treatment.


2


I self-diagnosis medicine, fever to eat some anti-fever medicine, nutrition, high-protein, high-energy food, survived the most difficult days, fever. But here's the other bad news. As I returned home on the night of January 17, my wife, two daughters, and in-laws began to develop symptoms of fever, cough, and fatigue.

They're infected with me.

I've been a doctor for almost 20 years, and I've never been nervous about anything. What disease haven't I seen before? Bird Flu, AIDS, and many highly infectious diseases, I have seen, but also not afraid of. But this time, I was scared.

That feeling is a sense of powerlessness beyond your expertise and your ability to control a virus. Usually we ICU is for all patients to guarantee the bottom, each department can not handle, we can handle. But now, we can't be sure of anyone else. We won the bid ourselves. Like, the last line of Defense, gone.

I've never been so helpless. I'm not afraid of the virus. I'm afraid of my family. Although they are still mild illness, under my treatment is also gradually recovering, but I always worry, the family elderly, loved ones after a dozen days there will be repeated? What will their lungs look like? What about the aftereffects? No one can answer, no one has experience..

And all of this, it's my fault.
As a doctor, you can't protect your own family. Who Do you think you can protect?


3


February 3rd was supposed to be my best day in a while. Because the old man's stable. The other day when they couldn't get out of bed because they were tired, I was really, really anxious.

These days, when I have free time, I also use the public number of our hospital for fever patients online. January 28,8:00 pm for the first time online, a breath to see one or two late at night, plus the next morning, a total of about 200 people saw. In fact, in order to ensure the quality of medical care, the hospital limited us to see a maximum of 50 people a day. I set it to 200 as soon as I got online, as if I could handle so many emergency calls. But I didn't expect to exceed the standard on the first day. The next day, I adjusted it to 300... and now I'll have as many patients as I can get. Turn on your phone, and there's a constant stream of requests, and the phone just won't keep up.
Image | visual China
Fever patients, mostly. Some are living in isolation at home; some are considering new pneumonia but have not seen it; some have no beds and do not know what to do; and some are asking what to do for the elderly and pregnant women in their current situation; Someone introduced themselves to the trail for a while and asked me if there was any chance of infection... I could sense that these patients were terrified and helpless. Everyone is helpless.

Before the patient on-line Consults, it is to upload case picture commonly, casually type A few word, simple ask. Now I see advice written in thousands of words. I can even imagine, on the other side of the screen, people in their sixty, spending hours on their phones, typing these words. They must have had no choice. They had no choice but to try and find some hope in this way.

To tell the truth, if it is new coronary pneumonia, the way through the online consultation, also can not help them to solve any real problem. But it would be nice if my response gave even a small measure of hope to the anxious and panicky.

In a minute, I'm GonNa double-check, and if the nucleic acid test turns negative and it's not contagious, I'm GONNA have to go back to work. We're running out of doctors here. I'm GONNA fill in. Guys, I'M ALMOST BACK! When this thing blows over, I want to hold my baby.

My grand princess and my little princess,
I haven't held them in a long time.

(the Chinese doctor is a recipient of the bytedance medical workers humanitarian relief fund of the China Red Cross Foundation. At the request of the recipient, Li Chun is a pseudonym.)

Chinese Red Cross Foundation bytedance medical workers humanitarian relief fund
On January 25,2020, bytedance, the parent company of Toutiao, Douyin and watermelon video, donated 200 million RMB to the Red Cross Foundation of China to establish the bytedance medical workers humanitarian relief fund of the Red Cross Foundation of China, to fight the epidemic front-line medical workers to provide security.
As of February 3,2020, the Special Fund has provided humanitarian relief to a total of 67 first-line medical workers in seven batches to combat the epidemic. Among them, 64 first-line medical staff who died in the fight against the epidemic were each given a subsidy of 100,000 yuan, and 3 first-line medical staff who died in the line of duty due to the fight against the epidemic were each given a subsidy of 1 million yuan per family.

My grand princess and my little princess,
I haven't held them in a long time.

(the Chinese doctor is a recipient of the bytedance medical workers humanitarian relief fund of the China Red Cross Foundation. At the request of the recipient, Li Chun is a pseudonym.)

Chinese Red Cross Foundation bytedance medical workers humanitarian relief fund
On January 25,2020, bytedance, the parent company of Toutiao, Douyin and watermelon video, donated 200 million RMB to the Red Cross Foundation of China to establish the bytedance medical workers humanitarian relief fund of the Red Cross Foundation of China, to fight the epidemic front-line medical workers to provide security.
As of February 3,2020, the Special Fund has provided humanitarian relief to a total of 67 first-line medical workers in seven batches to combat the epidemic. Among them, 64 first-line medical staff who died in the fight against the epidemic were each given a subsidy of 100,000 yuan, and 3 first-line medical staff who died in the line of duty due to the fight against the epidemic were each given a subsidy of 1 million yuan per family.

Chinese Red Cross Foundation bytedance medical workers humanitarian relief fund
On January 25,2020, bytedance, the parent company of Toutiao, Douyin and watermelon video, donated 200 million RMB to the Red Cross Foundation of China to establish the bytedance medical workers humanitarian relief fund of the Red Cross Foundation of China, to fight the epidemic front-line medical workers to provide security.
As of February 3,2020, the Special Fund has provided humanitarian relief to a total of 67 first-line medical workers in seven batches to combat the epidemic. Among them, 64 first-line medical staff who died in the fight against the epidemic were each given a subsidy of 100,000 yuan, and 3 first-line medical staff who died in the line of duty due to the fight against the epidemic were each given a subsidy of 1 million yuan per family.
